prvtPwVcTDMMIB.name: prvtPwVcTDMMIB

revisions.description: Update interval values for : prvtPwVcTDMCfgPeerPort prvtPwVcTDMCfgLocalPort prvtPwVcTDMCfgOosPort prvtPwVcTDMCfgPeerOosPort
Change the range for prvtPwVcTDMCfgChannelGroup in order to support all configurable channels group for OC3 module
Added Oos Ecid and Vlan priotity objects.

prvtPwVcTDMMIB.contactinfo: BATM/Telco Systems Support team Email: For North America: techsupport@telco.com For North Europe: support@batm.de, info@batm.de For the rest of the world: techsupport@telco.com
prvtPwVcTDMMIB.description: This MIB contains managed object definitions for encapsulating TDM (T1, E1, T3, E3, NxDS0) as pseudo-wires over packet-switching networks (PSN).

PrvtPwVcTDMCfgIndex.name: PrvtPwVcTDMCfgIndex
PrvtPwVcTDMCfgIndex.description: Index into any of the relevant prvtPwVcXXXCfgTable.

TimeSlotList.name: TimeSlotList
TimeSlotList.description: Each octet within this value specifies a time slot included in the give channel group. There should be 32 bits of 4 octets for each port of the CES module. Note that if the line type is set to T1 only the first 24 bits of each 4 octests can be set. The most significant bit of the list indicates timeslot 1 of port 1, the 33th bit - timeslot 1 of port 2, etc. If the bit is set, the port is included in the given channel group.

PrvtPwVcTDMCfgInterface.name: PrvtPwVcTDMCfgInterface
PrvtPwVcTDMCfgInterface.description: Interface of the given circuit used in TDM config for OC3 modules

InterfaceTimeSlot.name: InterfaceTimeSlot
InterfaceTimeSlot.description: The first 4 octets of this value represent the interface of the given channel group P.K.L.M.The last 32 bits of the 4 octets represent a bitmask of the time slots

prvtPwVcTDMTable.name: prvtPwVcTDMTable
prvtPwVcTDMTable.description: This table contains basic information including ifIndex, and pointers to entries in the relevant TDM config tables for this TDM PW.

prvtPwVcTDMEntry.name: prvtPwVcTDMEntry
prvtPwVcTDMEntry.description: This table is indexed by the same index that was created for the associated entry in the PW Table (in the PW-STD-MIB). An entry is created in this table by the agent for every entry in the prvtPwVcTable with a prvtPwVcType of 'TDM'.

prvtPwVcTDMModuleId.name: prvtPwVcTDMModuleId
prvtPwVcTDMModuleId.description: The ID of the CES Module where the crcuit is configured.

prvtPwVcTDMCircuitId.name: prvtPwVcTDMCircuitId
prvtPwVcTDMCircuitId.description: The ID of the CES Circuit that this PW represents.

prvtPwVcTDMType.name: prvtPwVcTDMType
prvtPwVcTDMType.description: Specifies the type of TDM PW. The connection assumed to be symmetrical having the same value at both ends. To identify structured vs. unstructured type for DS1 and E1, dsx1LineType and dsx1SignalMode [DS1MIB] should be referenced. DS3 and E3 are always unstructured.

prvtPwVcRelTDMCfgIndex.name: prvtPwVcRelTDMCfgIndex
prvtPwVcRelTDMCfgIndex.description: Index to the relevant TDM configuration table entry that appears in one of the related MIB modules such as SAToP, TDMoIP or CESoPSN. It is likely that multiple TDM PWs of the same characteristic will share a single configuration entry of the relevant type.

prvtPwVcTDMTimeElapsed.name: prvtPwVcTDMTimeElapsed
prvtPwVcTDMTimeElapsed.description: The number of seconds, including partial seconds, that have elapsed since the beginning of the current measurement period. If, for some reason, such as an adjustment in the system's time-of-day clock, the current interval exceeds the maximum value, the agent will return the maximum value.

prvtPwVcTDMValidIntervals.name: prvtPwVcTDMValidIntervals
prvtPwVcTDMValidIntervals.description: The number of previous 15-minute intervals for which data was collected. An agent with TDM capability must be capable of supporting at least n intervals. The minimum value of n is 4, The default of n is 32 and the maximum value of n is 96. The value will be <n> unless the measurement was (re-) started within the last (<n>*15) minutes, in which case the value will be the number of complete 15 minute intervals for which the agent has at least some data. In certain cases(e.g., in the case where the agent is a proxy) it is possible that some intervals are unavailable. In this case, this interval is the maximum interval number for which data is available.

prvtPwVcTDMCurrentIndications.name: prvtPwVcTDMCurrentIndications
prvtPwVcTDMCurrentIndications.description: The following defects should be detected and reported upon request: -Stray packets MAY be detected by the PSN and multiplexing layers. Stray packets MUST be discarded by the CE-bound IWF and their detection MUST NOT affect mechanisms for detection of packet loss. -Malformed packets are detected by mismatch between the expected packet size (taking the value of the L bit into account) and the actual packet size inferred from the PSN and multiplexing layers. Malformed in-order packets MUST be discarded by the CE-bound IWF and replacement data generated as for lost packets. -Excessive packet loss rate is detected by computing the average packet loss rate over the value of prvtPwVcTDMAvePktLossTimeWindow and comparing it with a preconfigured threshold [SATOP]. -Buffer overrun is detected in the normal operation state when the CE bound IWF's jitter buffer cannot accommodate newly arrived packets. -Remote packet loss is indicated by reception of packets with their R bit set. -Packet misorder is detected by looking at the Sequence number provided by the control word. -TDM Fault, if L bit in the control word is set, it indicates that TDM data carried in the payload is invalid due an attachment circuit fault. When the L bit is set the payload MAY be omitted in order to conserve bandwidth. Note: the algorithm used to capture these indications is implementation specific.

prvtPwVcTDMLatchedIndications.name: prvtPwVcTDMLatchedIndications
prvtPwVcTDMLatchedIndications.description: The state of TDM indicators when the TDM PW last declared an error second (either as ES, SES or a second with errors inside a UAS) condition. At this time, only LOPS can create a failure. Since indicators other than LOPS are useful, all are latched here. For bit definitions, see prvtPwVcTDMCurrentIndications above. Note: the algorithm used to latch these indications when entering an defect state is implementation specific.

prvtPwVcTDMLastEsTimeStamp.name: prvtPwVcTDMLastEsTimeStamp
prvtPwVcTDMLastEsTimeStamp.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion at which the TDM PW entered the ES or SES state.

prvtPwVcTDMOperStatus.name: prvtPwVcTDMOperStatus
prvtPwVcTDMOperStatus.description: The operational status of the circuit.

prvtPwVcTDMCfgTable.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgTable
prvtPwVcTDMCfgTable.description: This table contains a set of parameters that may be referenced by one or more TDM PWs in prvtPwVcTDMTable.

prvtPwVcTDMCfgEntry.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgEntry
prvtPwVcTDMCfgEntry.description: These parameters define the characteristics of a TDM PW. They are grouped here to ease NMS burden. Once an entry is created here it may be re-used by many PWs.

prvtPwVcTDMCfgPayloadSize.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgPayloadSize
prvtPwVcTDMCfgPayloadSize.description: The value of this object indicates the PayLoad Size to be defined during the PW setUp. Upon TX, implementation must be capable of carrying that amount of data. Upon RX, When the LEN field is set to 0, the payload of packet MUST assume this size, and if the actual packet size is inconsistent with this length, the packet MUST be considered to be malformed.

prvtPwVcTDMCfgPktReorder.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgPktReorder
prvtPwVcTDMCfgPktReorder.description: If set True: as CE bound packets are queued in the jitter buffer, out of order packets are re-ordered. The maximum sequence number differential (i.e., the range in which re-sequencing can occur) is dependant on the depth of the jitter buffer. See prvtPwVcTDMCfgJtrBfrDepth. NOTE: Some implementations may not support this feature. The agent is then required to set this False.

prvtPwVcTDMCfgRtpHdrUsed.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgRtpHdrUsed
prvtPwVcTDMCfgRtpHdrUsed.description: If set False: an RTP header is not pre-pended to the TDM packet.

prvtPwVcTDMCfgJtrBfrDepth.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgJtrBfrDepth
prvtPwVcTDMCfgJtrBfrDepth.description: The size of the Jitter buffer SHOULD be defined to a value that is capable to allow accommodation to the PSN-specific packet delay variation. If configured to a value not supported by the implementation, the agent MUST return an error code 'jtrBfrDepth' in 'prvtPwVcTDMConfigError ' NOTE: jitter buffers are a limited resource to be managed.

prvtPwVcTDMCfgChannelGroup.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgChannelGroup
prvtPwVcTDMCfgChannelGroup.description: The circuit's channel group. This object is only valid if structured emulation mode is used. If a group is not set the value of the object is 0.

prvtPwVcTDMCfgPorts.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgPorts
prvtPwVcTDMCfgPorts.description: A bitmap of themodule's TDM ports belongng to the circuit.

prvtPwVcTDMCfgPeerIpType.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgPeerIpType
prvtPwVcTDMCfgPeerIpType.description: The type of the peer's IP address.

prvtPwVcTDMCfgPeerMAC.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgPeerMAC
prvtPwVcTDMCfgPeerMAC.description: The Peer MAC address. This object is only valid for Metro-Ethernet and Mpls circuits. If an IP address is configured for the circuit, this object will display the resolved MAC address.

prvtPwVcTDMCfgPeerEcid.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgPeerEcid
prvtPwVcTDMCfgPeerEcid.description: The peer circuit identifier. This object is only valid if the Circuit protocol is metro-ethernet.

prvtPwVcTDMCfgPeerOosEcid.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgPeerOosEcid
prvtPwVcTDMCfgPeerOosEcid.description: The peer circuit identifier for the out-of-band signaling. This value is valid only when the object prvtPwVcTDMCfgEcid is set and when the current protocol is metro-ethernet

prvtPwVcTDMCfgVlanPrio.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgVlanPrio
prvtPwVcTDMCfgVlanPrio.description: The prioirty for the VLAN set here, when the protocol for the circuit is metro-ethernet

prvtPwVcTDMCfgEcid.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgEcid
prvtPwVcTDMCfgEcid.description: The local circuit identifier. This object is only valid if the Circuit protocol is metro-ethernet.

prvtPwVcTDMCfgOosEcid.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgOosEcid
prvtPwVcTDMCfgOosEcid.description: The local circuit identifier for the out-of-band signaling. This value is valid only when the object prvtPwVcTDMCfgEcid is set and when the current protocol is metro-ethernet

prvtPwVcTDMCfgAdminStatus.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgAdminStatus
prvtPwVcTDMCfgAdminStatus.description: The administrative status of the circuit.

prvtPwVcTDMCfgRowStatus.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgRowStatus
prvtPwVcTDMCfgRowStatus.description: This field is used to create and destroy TDM circuits.

prvtPwVcTDMCfgPayloadSuppression.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgPayloadSuppression
prvtPwVcTDMCfgPayloadSuppression.description: Controls payload suppression. Object does not require module to be restarted.

prvtPwVcTDMCfgInterface.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgInterface
prvtPwVcTDMCfgInterface.description: Interface used for configuring OC3 TDM circuits P - Port Number, K, L, M standard numbering of SONET/SDH.

prvtPwVcTDMCfgIpOosTos.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgIpOosTos
prvtPwVcTDMCfgIpOosTos.description: Set/Show IP Out Of Stream information

prvtPwVcTDMCfgPeerOosPort.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgPeerOosPort
prvtPwVcTDMCfgPeerOosPort.description: This field is used to SET Destination Oos Port

prvtPwVcTDMCfgMplsLocalLabel.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgMplsLocalLabel
prvtPwVcTDMCfgMplsLocalLabel.description: The local circuit identifier. This object is only valid if the Circuit protocol is MPLS

prvtPwVcTDMCfgMplsPeerLabel.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgMplsPeerLabel
prvtPwVcTDMCfgMplsPeerLabel.description: The peer circuit identifier. This object is only valid if the Circuit protocol is MPLS

prvtPwVcTDMCfgMplsOosLocalLabel.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgMplsOosLocalLabel
prvtPwVcTDMCfgMplsOosLocalLabel.description: The local circuit identifier for the out-of-band signaling. This object is only valid if the Circuit protocol is MPLS

prvtPwVcTDMCfgMplsOosPeerLabel.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgMplsOosPeerLabel
prvtPwVcTDMCfgMplsOosPeerLabel.description: The peer circuit identifier for the out-of-band signaling. This object is only valid if the Circuit protocol is MPLS

prvtPwVcTDMCfgMplsOosTTL.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgMplsOosTTL
prvtPwVcTDMCfgMplsOosTTL.description: MPLS TTL for the out-of-band signaling.

prvtPwVcTDMCfgMplsOosExp.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgMplsOosExp
prvtPwVcTDMCfgMplsOosExp.description: MPLS EXP for the out-of-band signaling.

prvtPwVcTDMCfgRtpOosPayload.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgRtpOosPayload
prvtPwVcTDMCfgRtpOosPayload.description: This field is used to SET RTP Oos payload type.

prvtPwVcTDMCfgRtpPayload.name: prvtPwVcTDMCfgRtpPayload
prvtPwVcTDMCfgRtpPayload.description: This field is used to SET RTP payload type.

prvtTDMChannelGrpTable.name: prvtTDMChannelGrpTable
prvtTDMChannelGrpTable.description: This table contains the set of available channel groups.

prvtTDMChannelGrpEntry.name: prvtTDMChannelGrpEntry
prvtTDMChannelGrpEntry.description: These parameters are used to configure a CES channel group.

prvtTDMChannelGrpModuleID.name: prvtTDMChannelGrpModuleID
prvtTDMChannelGrpModuleID.description: The index of the module to which this channel group belongs.

prvtTDMChannelGrpCfgError.name: prvtTDMChannelGrpCfgError
prvtTDMChannelGrpCfgError.description: This object displays the correctness of the configuration. If it has a value of channelGroupAtached(1) this channel group has been attached to a circuit and the new configuration cannot be applied.

prvtTDMChannelGrpTimeSlots.name: prvtTDMChannelGrpTimeSlots
prvtTDMChannelGrpTimeSlots.description: This object is used to configure which time slots are members of the given channel group.

prvtTDMChannelGrpOC3TimeSlots.name: prvtTDMChannelGrpOC3TimeSlots
prvtTDMChannelGrpOC3TimeSlots.description: This object is used to configure interface and time slots for the given channel group in OC3 module.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentTable.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentTable
prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentTable.description: The current 15 minute interval counts are in this table. This table provides per TDM PW performance information.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentEntry.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentEntry
prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentEntry.description: An entry in this table is created by the agent for every prvtPwVcTDM entry. After 15 minutes, the contents of this table entry are copied to a new entry in the prvtPwVcTDMPerfInterval table and the counts in this entry are reset to zero.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentPktsOoseq.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentPktsOoseq
prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentPktsOoseq.description: Number of packets detected out of sequence (via TDM header sequence numbers), but successfully re-ordered. Note: some implementations may not support this Feature.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentJtrBfrUnderruns.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentJtrBfrUnderruns
prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentJtrBfrUnderruns.description: Number of times a packet needed to be played out and the jitter buffer was empty.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentJtrBfrOverruns.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentJtrBfrOverruns
prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentJtrBfrOverruns.description: Number of packets detected out of range (via TDM header sequence numbers), and could not be re- ordered, or could not fit in the jitter buffer.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentMalformedPkt.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentMalformedPkt
prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentMalformedPkt.description: Number of packets detected with unexpected size, or bad headers' stack

prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalTable.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalTable
prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalTable.description: This table provides performance information per TDM PW similar to the prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentTable above. However, these counts represent historical 15 minute intervals. Typically, this table will have a maximum of 96 entries for a 24 hour period, but is not limited to this.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalEntry.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalEntry
prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalEntry.description: An entry in this table is created by the agent for every prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentEntry that is 15 minutes old. The contents of the Current entry are copied to the new entry here. The Current entry, then resets its counts to zero for the next current 15 minute interval.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalNumber.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalNumber
prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalNumber.description: A number (normally between 1 and 96 to cover a 24 hour period) which identifies the interval for which the set of statistics is available. The interval identified by 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval, and the interval identified by N is the interval immediately preceding the one identified by N-1. The minimum range of N is 1 through 4. The default range is 1 through 32. The maximum value of N is 1 through 96.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalValidData.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalValidData
prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalValidData.description: This variable indicates if the data for this interval is valid.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalDuration.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalDuration
prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalDuration.description: The duration of a particular interval in seconds, Adjustments in the system's time-of-day clock, may cause the interval to be greater or less than, the normal value. Therefore this actual interval value is provided.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalPktsOoseq.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalPktsOoseq
prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalPktsOoseq.description: Number of packets detected out of sequence (via TDM header sequence numbers), but successfully re-ordered. Note: some implementations mat not support this feature.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalJtrBfrUnderruns.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalJtrBfrUnderruns
prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalJtrBfrUnderruns.description: Number of times a packet needed to be played out and the jitter buffer was empty.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalJtrBfrOverruns.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalJtrBfrOverruns
prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalJtrBfrOverruns.description: Number of packets detected out of range (via TDM header sequence numbers), and could not be re- ordered, or could not fit in the jitter buffer.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalMalformedPkt.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalMalformedPkt
prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalMalformedPkt.description: Number of packets detected with unexpected size, or bad headers' stack

prvtPwVcTDMPerfTable.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfTable
prvtPwVcTDMPerfTable.description: This table provides performance information per TDM PW similar to the prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalTable above. However, these counters represent complete historical information.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfEntry.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfEntry
prvtPwVcTDMPerfEntry.description: An entry is created in this table by the agent for every entry in the prvtPwVcTDM table.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfPktsOoseq.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfPktsOoseq
prvtPwVcTDMPerfPktsOoseq.description: Number of packets detected out of sequence (via TDM header sequence numbers), but successfully re-ordered. Note: some implementations may not support this feature.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfJtrBfrUnderruns.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfJtrBfrUnderruns
prvtPwVcTDMPerfJtrBfrUnderruns.description: Number of times a packet needed to be played out and the jitter buffer was empty.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfJtrBfrOverruns.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfJtrBfrOverruns
prvtPwVcTDMPerfJtrBfrOverruns.description: Number of packets detected out of range (via TDM header sequence numbers), and could not be re- ordered, or could not fit in the jitter buffer.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfMalformedPkt.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfMalformedPkt
prvtPwVcTDMPerfMalformedPkt.description: Number of packets detected with unexpected size, or bad headers' stack.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfDiscontinuityTime.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfDiscontinuityTime
prvtPwVcTDMPerfDiscontinuityTime.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion at which any one or more of this segment's Counter32 suffered a discontinuity. If no such discontinuities have occurred since the last re- initialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

prvtPwVcTDMAlarmTable.name: prvtPwVcTDMAlarmTable
prvtPwVcTDMAlarmTable.description: This table contains object for configuring and displaying CES Circuits TCA thresholds.

prvtPwVcTDMAlarmIndex.name: prvtPwVcTDMAlarmIndex
prvtPwVcTDMAlarmIndex.description: An integer uniquely identifying an alarm entry.

prvtPwVcTDMAlarmVariable.name: prvtPwVcTDMAlarmVariable
prvtPwVcTDMAlarmVariable.description: The OID of the variable whose value is being monitored. Depending on the time interval, the error condition and the modue and circuit ID, this points to an object from an entry in prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentTable or prvtPwVcTDMPerfTable.

prvtPwVcTDMAlarmThreshold.name: prvtPwVcTDMAlarmThreshold
prvtPwVcTDMAlarmThreshold.description: The alarm condition threshold for this alarm entry. The alarm is triggered if the value of the object pointed by prvtPwVcTDMAlarmVariable remains above this threshold for more than 3 seconds.

prvtPwVcTDMAlarmValue.name: prvtPwVcTDMAlarmValue
prvtPwVcTDMAlarmValue.description: The value of the object pointed to by prvtPwVcTDMAlarmVariable, present for notification purposes.

prvtPwVcTDMAlarm.name: prvtPwVcTDMAlarm
prvtPwVcTDMAlarm.description: This notification is sent when the value of a TDM port error condition statistic has exceeded the configured threshold, or the value has dropped back below the threshold.

prvtPwVcTDMStatusChange.name: prvtPwVcTDMStatusChange
prvtPwVcTDMStatusChange.description: This notification is sent when the operational or administrative status of circuit changes.

prvtPwTDMModuleCompliance.name: prvtPwTDMModuleCompliance
prvtPwTDMModuleCompliance.description: The compliance statement for agent that support PW over TDM PSN operation.

prvtPwVcTDMGroup.name: prvtPwVcTDMGroup
prvtPwVcTDMGroup.description: Collection of objects for basic TDM PW config and status.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentGroup.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentGroup
prvtPwVcTDMPerfCurrentGroup.description: Collection of current statistics objects for TDM PWs.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalGroup.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalGroup
prvtPwVcTDMPerfIntervalGroup.description: Collection of Interval statistics objects for TDM PWs.

prvtPwVcTDMPerfGroup.name: prvtPwVcTDMPerfGroup
prvtPwVcTDMPerfGroup.description: Collection of running statistics objects for TDM PWs.
